  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nI am running lighthouse under systemd (fedora 32 server).  The lighthouse.service file prefers a PIDFile=<filepath> entry for services with Type=forking so systemd can identify the main service process. Provide an optional --pidfile=<filepath> option for lighthouse so I can specify the PID file location (typically /run/... on Fedora).  Provide a --daemon (and/or --background) option to detach lighthouse from the terminal.\r\nUsing Type=Simple in the lighthouse.service file does not give the same level of process control as with Type=Forking.\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\n$ lighthouse --version\r\nLighthouse v0.2.11-b8013b7b\r\nBLS Library: blst\r\n\r\n$ rustc --version\r\nrustc 1.45.2\r\n\r\n$ git describe --tags HEAD\r\nv0.2.11-7-gb8013b7b\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nNo lighthouse --pidfile option is available and hence no easy way to record the lighthouse PID to a file.  No --daemon (and/or --background) option available to cause the process to fork.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nProvide an optional --pidfile option to lighthouse to record the lighthouse PID to a file.  Provide a --daemon (and/or --background) option to cause the process to fork.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nUsing Type=Simple in the lighthouse.service file is possible but systemd does not have as much process control as with Type=Forking and a PID file.\r\n",
